The '''2nd parallel south''' is a [[circle of latitude]] that is 2 [[degree (angle)|degrees]] [[south]] of the [[Earth|Earth's]] [[equator|equatorial plane]]. It crosses the [[Atlantic Ocean]], [[Africa]], the [[Indian Ocean]], [[Southeast Asia]], [[Australasia]], the [[Pacific Ocean]] and [[South America]].

==Around the world==
Starting at the [[prime meridian]] and heading eastwards, the parallel 2° south passes through:

